config BOXFS_FS
	tristate "Box archive filesystem support"
	depends on RUST
	help
	  Box is a read-only archive format optimized for fast random access
	  and efficient storage. This filesystem allows mounting .box archives
	  directly.

	  Box archives support:
	  - Zstd and XZ compression
	  - Extended attributes
	  - Symlinks (internal and external)
	  - Efficient directory indexing via FST

	  To compile this as a module, choose M here: the module will be
	  called boxfs.

	  If unsure, say N.
